The following files are MODIFIED versions of files originally from vLLM and/or the
community `kyuz0/vllm-therock-gfx1151` image, redistributed here under Apache-2.0
with the modifications described below:

- pytorch_patched.py
    Original: vllm/model_executor/kernels/linear/scaled_mm/pytorch.py (vLLM, Apache-2.0)
    Modification: route FP8 (W8A8) matmuls to the custom Triton dequant-GEMV in
    fp8_triton.py instead of torch._scaled_mm (which is unsupported on RDNA/gfx1151).

- rocm_patched.py
    Original: vllm/platforms/rocm.py (vLLM, Apache-2.0; the APU VRAM workaround
    block originates from the kyuz0/vllm-therock-gfx1151 image).
    Modification: _patched_mem_info reads BOTH mem_info_vram_total and
    mem_info_gtt_total and uses max(...), so the dedicated-VRAM BIOS layout reports
    the full pool (the stock patch read GTT only and broke that layout).

- triton_scaled_mm_patched.py
    Original: vllm/model_executor/layers/quantization/compressed_tensors/triton_scaled_mm.py
    (vLLM, Apache-2.0).
    Modification: route M==1 (decode) of the W8A8-INT8 path to the rows-mapped
    dequant-GEMV in fp8_triton.py (gated by env FP8_GEMV_DECODE, symmetric quant);
    falls back to the stock Triton GEMM for prefill / asymmetric / on error.

- nvfp4_emulation_utils_patched.py
    Original: vllm/model_executor/layers/quantization/utils/nvfp4_emulation_utils.py
    (vLLM, Apache-2.0).
    Modification: route M==1 (decode, swizzle=False) of run_nvfp4_emulations to the
    fused FP4 dequant-GEMV in nvfp4_triton.py (gated by env NVFP4_GEMV), avoiding the
    full-bf16-weight materialization; falls back to the stock emulation otherwise.

fp8_triton.py, nvfp4_triton.py, and the scripts under bench/ are original work.
